&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About BluShark Digital:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BluShark Digital is a digital marketing agency focused on helping law firms and professional service businesses grow through search engine optimization, digital strategy, and measurable online visibility. We are a client-first, results-driven company that combines data, strategy, and relationship-building to help businesses compete in highly competitive markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a motivated and personable Business Development Representative to support both outbound appointment setting and event-driven business development. This is a hybrid role for someone comfortable working leads from a CRM, executing structured outreach campaigns, and representing BluShark in person at conferences, trade shows, and industry events.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Approach to Business Development:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BluShark’s business development approach is consultative, relationship-driven, and reputation-conscious. We are not looking for someone to create artificial conversations, force appointments, or push prospects into meetings that do not make sense.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is about identifying businesses that may genuinely benefit from BluShark’s services, starting thoughtful conversations, understanding their goals and challenges, and helping determine whether a deeper consultation would be valuable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe strong business development begins with trust. Our team is expected to represent BluShark as a knowledgeable and professional partner, not as a transactional vendor. The goal is not simply to “book meetings.” The goal is to create qualified, meaningful opportunities where BluShark can provide insight, guidance, and potential value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should be comfortable with outbound activity and follow-up, but they should also understand that our reputation depends on how we show up in every interaction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*PLEASE NOTE - this is a remote position, however we would prefer candidates based on the east coast who are willing to travel to our Washington D.C. office as needed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Business Development Representative will be responsible for generating qualified sales conversations through outbound outreach, lead nurturing, conference follow-up, and in-person event engagement. This role blends traditional BDR responsibilities with relationship-based business development for event and conference business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a high-pressure appointment-setting role focused on volume for volume’s sake. The right candidate will know how to identify prospects who may genuinely benefit from BluShark’s services, clearly communicate value, ask thoughtful questions, and help determine whether a consultation is the appropriate next step.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is organized, confident, personable, and persistent. They should be comfortable making calls, sending emails, managing HubSpot tasks, following up consistently, and having professional conversations with business owners, attorneys, executives, and referral partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Success in this role depends on two core abilities: disciplined CRM-based sales execution and the interpersonal skill to create meaningful, reputation-enhancing opportunities in live-event environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outbound Sales &amp;amp; Appointment Setting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct outbound outreach through phone, email, text, LinkedIn, and other approved channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, qualify, and nurture prospective clients who may benefit from BluShark’s services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help convert qualified, relevant conversations into appropriate discovery or co

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Title:&lt;/strong&gt; Contractor - Event &amp;amp; Conference Business Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BluShark Digital is a digital marketing agency focused on helping law firms and professional service businesses grow through search engine optimization, digital strategy, and measurable online visibility. We regularly attend industry conferences, trade shows, and networking events to build relationships, educate prospective clients, and create new business opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an Event &amp;amp; Conference Business Development Contractor to represent BluShark at selected events throughout the year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Approach to Business Development:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BluShark’s business development approach is consultative, relationship-driven, and reputation-conscious. We are not looking for someone to create artificial conversations, force appointments, or push prospects into meetings that do not make sense.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is about identifying businesses that may genuinely benefit from BluShark’s services, starting thoughtful conversations, understanding their goals and challenges, and helping determine whether a deeper consultation would be valuable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe strong business development begins with trust. Our team is expected to represent BluShark as a knowledgeable and professional partner, not as a transactional vendor. The goal is not simply to “book meetings.” The goal is to create qualified, meaningful opportunities where BluShark can provide insight, guidance, and potential value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is especially important at conferences, where every conversation contributes to BluShark’s reputation in the market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Event &amp;amp; Conference Business Development Contractor will support BluShark’s in-person business development efforts at conferences, trade shows, networking events, and industry gatherings. This contractor will help create conversations, capture leads, qualify interest, and support appointment-setting efforts during and after events.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a contractor role, not a full-time employee position. Work will be assigned on an event-by-event basis depending on the conference calendar, geographic location, availability, and fit for the event.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal contractor is personable, professional, confident in live networking environments, and capable of representing BluShark in a polished and credible manner.&amp;nbsp;They should be able to create natural conversations, listen for real business needs, and identify whether there may be a meaningful opportunity for BluShark to help.&lt;/p&gt;
