&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced and detail-oriented Controller to oversee the company&#39;s accounting operations, financial reporting, budgeting, and internal controls. The Controller will ensure the accuracy and integrity of financial records while providing strategic financial insights to support business growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience supporting professional services organizations is highly preferred, particularly within law firms, legal marketing agencies, digital marketing agencies, or other fast-paced, client-service businesses with complex financial operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*This position is based in Washington, DC and follows a hybrid work schedule. Candidates must be able to reliably commute to the office on designated in-office days.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee all day-to-day accounting operations, including accounts payable, accounts receivable, payroll, general ledger, and bank reconciliations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage attorney trust accounts and ensure compliance with applicable regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare accurate monthly, quarterly, and annual financial statements and management reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the month-end and year-end close processes, ensuring timely and accurate reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, maintain, and improve accounting policies, procedures, and internal controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage cash flow forecasting and monitor the company&#39;s financial position.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare annual budgets and financial forecasts while providing variance analysis and recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with GAAP and all federal, state, and local financial reporting requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee tax filings, business licenses, and regulatory reporting requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze financial performance and provide strategic recommendations to leadership regarding profitability, cost management, and operational efficiencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support executive leadership with financial modeling, scenario planning, and special projects as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with system implementations, process automation, and continuous improvement initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Accounting, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting professional services such as law firms or legal marketing agencies preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of progressive accounting experience, with at least 2 years in a Controller or senior accounting leadership role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of GAAP and financial reporting requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing the full accounting cycle and financial close process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Excel and accounting software (QuickBooks, NetSuite, Sage Intacct, or similar ERP systems).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with payroll systems and financial planning tools is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical, organizational, and problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing and improving financial processes and internal controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong business acumen with the ability to translate financial data into actionable insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting executive leadership with strategic financial planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of budgeting, forecasting, and cash flow management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High level of integrity, discretion, and professionalism when handling confidential financial information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
